What Is the Process to Request a Custom Crating Quote in Las Vegas?
To get a quote, provide measurements, photos and destination details so a provider can estimate materials and labor and determine whether ISPM‑15 treatment or special handling is required. An on‑site assessment confirms access, suggests optimal crate orientation and lets the team plan for floor protection and workspace during in‑home assembly. Quote turnaround depends on complexity but should include a clear breakdown of materials, labor hours, optional white‑glove handling and certification costs. Homeowners who supply detailed information up front typically receive faster, more accurate estimates with fewer revisions.

Including an estimated insurance value and any required documents up front helps the crating provider prepare condition reports and labeling for smoother transit or storage.

What Should Homeowners Expect During the Custom Crating Experience?
Expect a scheduled arrival window, protective measures for floors and paths, step‑by‑step assembly of internal supports and photographic documentation of the item and completed crate for your records. Crating teams usually provide on‑site time estimates and will ask that you clear space around the item for safe, efficient assembly. After the crate is built, you’ll receive tags, handling instructions and condition photos to keep for insurance or future reference. Delivery options can include white‑glove setup and reassembly at your destination or secure pickup for local storage or transport.

Prepare the space for on‑site assembly by clearing walkways and protecting floors.
